page.title: 14LEASOWE SHORE MARINE LIFE(1)
page.content:
Leasowe shoreline stretches from Leasowe to Moreton, and borders Liverpool Bay (Irish Sea). Its historical name is{Mockbeggar Wharf.} { Despite many worries of pollution from Merseyside industry we still found many examples of marine life existing.
Here are some examples of marine life we found on Leasowe Shore:{ { {1) Common Shore Crab (Carcinus Maenas) 2) Common Mussel (Mytilus Edulus) {3) Star Barnacle(Chthamalus Stellatus) 4) Common Jellysish (Aurelia Aurita) {5) Common Whelk (Buccinum Undatum) 6) Egg Mass of common Dogfish {7) Chondrus Crispus (Irish moss or { Carragheen frond) { } (contd.)
